headline.main: ICKES DENOUNCES 'TRAITOR' ACTIVITY; He Declares That Dissidents to Popular Will of Nation Must Stand Aside

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Nov. 16 -- Harold L. Ickes, Secretary of the Interior, declared tonight that those dissidents "who consciously or unconsciously are playing the traitor's part" must stand aside while the nation marches toward the goal approved by an overwhelming majority -- the defeat of Hitler.
abstract: S at Fight for Freedom rally, Wash
